    {
      "id": "d5d093c1_13f7cbf9",
      "file_path": "cps-ncmp-service/src/main/java/org/onap/cps/ncmp/impl/inventory/sync/lcm/CmHandleStateMonitor.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 61,
      "message": "A couple of thoughts:\n- when restarting with an existing DB, the dataspace will already exist, so no exceptions are expected.\n- for DataspaceNotFound, then there would be no CM-handles anyway, so counters should be initialized to zero.\n- so your above solution should work fine. Maybe do some manual testing to verify.\n\nI think another option would be for this class to extend _ApplicationListener<ApplicationReadyEvent>_. Since inventory model is created during startup (_ApplicationStartedEvent_), needed model would be available before the application is ready.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6742,
        "name": "Daniel Hanrahan",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "daniel.hanrahan@est.tech",
        "username": "danielhanrahan"
      },
